# Documentation Layout (`doc/modules/ROOT/`)

## Directory Structure

```
doc/modules/ROOT/
├── nav.adoc
└── pages/
    ├── index.adoc
    ├── other-top-level.adoc
    ├── 2.topic-name/
    │   ├── 2.intro.adoc
    │   ├── 2a.first-sub.adoc
    │   └── 2b.second-sub.adoc
    └── 3.another-topic/
        ├── 3.intro.adoc
        ├── 3a.first-sub.adoc
        └── 3b.second-sub.adoc
```

## Root-Level Pages

- Live directly in `pages/` with no number prefix
- Examples: `index.adoc`, `quick-start.adoc`, `why-capy.adoc`
- kebab-case names

## Numbered Section Directories

- Format: `{N}.{topic-name}/` (e.g. `2.cpp20-coroutines/`, `5.buffers/`)
- Numbers are sequential; topic name is kebab-case

## Files Inside a Section

### Intro file: `{N}.intro.adoc`

- Every section directory has one
- If an intro already exists, keep it (rename to `{N}.intro.adoc` if needed)
- If none exists, create one with a compelling preface
- **NEVER** list or link to subsection pages
- Give a general overview that starts easy for beginners and naturally progresses to more technical material
- Must stay valid if subsections are added, removed, or reordered

### Subsection files: `{N}{letter}.{name}.adoc`

- Letters sequential starting at `a` (e.g. `4a.tasks.adoc`, `4b.launching.adoc`)
- **kebab-case** for general names (`7a.hello-task.adoc`)
- **PascalCase** when the name is a C++ concept or type (`8a.ReadStream.adoc`)
- **snake_case** only when matching an actual type name (`8i.any_buffer_sink.adoc`)

## File Headers

- Title as AsciiDoc level-1 heading (`= Title`)
- No YAML frontmatter

## nav.adoc

- Single `*` for root-level pages and section intro pages
- Double `**` for subsection pages nested under their section
- Entry order mirrors the file numbering

```
* xref:index.adoc[Introduction]
* xref:quick-start.adoc[Quick Start]
* xref:2.topic/2.intro.adoc[Topic Title]
** xref:2.topic/2a.first.adoc[First Subsection]
** xref:2.topic/2b.second.adoc[Second Subsection]
```

## No Extra Directories

Do not create `partials/`, `images/`, or `attachments/` subdirectories unless explicitly needed.
